userStories.notes:
Files:
- platform/cli/src/commands/plugin.ts (add TTY check to handlePluginConfigure)

Context:
handlePluginConfigure starts at platform/cli/src/commands/plugin.ts line 953. The function:
1. Finds the plugin dir
2. Reads configSchema
3. Reads current settings
4. Creates readline interface: `const rl = createInterface({ input: process.stdin, output: process.stdout });`
5. Loops calling promptField for each setting

prompField has inner while(true) loops for url-type fields that call rl.question() repeatedly. When stdin is EOF, rl.question() rejects/returns empty and the loop spins until the process crashes.

By contrast, promptForMissingArgs in scaffold.ts correctly handles this at lines 436-441:
```typescript
if (!process.stdin.isTTY) {
  const missing = [!name && 'name', !domain && '--domain'].filter(Boolean);
  throw new ScaffoldError(`Missing required arguments: ...`);
}
```

Changes:
Add this block AFTER the configSchema null check (line ~963) and BEFORE the readline interface creation (line ~975):

```typescript
if (!process.stdin.isTTY) {
  console.error(pc.red(`opentabs plugin configure requires an interactive terminal.`));
  console.error(`Use the non-interactive command instead:`);
  console.error(`  ${pc.cyan(`opentabs config set setting.${found.shortName}.<key> <value>`)}`);
  console.error(`  ${pc.dim(`Example: opentabs config set setting.${found.shortName}.instanceUrl https://example.com`)}`);
  process.exit(1);
}
```

Constraints:
- The check must occur AFTER the configSchema is loaded (so we have found.shortName available)
- Do NOT change the TTY flow (readline handling, promptField, settings save logic) — only add the guard
- Use pc.red/cyan/dim from the already-imported picocolors (pc)
